      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving masterpiece delivers a linear power band up to its 8,400 RPM redline, managed by a precise 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M differential lock. The chassis remains taut with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) providing optimal damping rates. Preventative maintenance is exhaustive, including documented rod bearing replacement with treated shells and refreshed throttle actuators. The Alpine White exterior retains its factory luster with zero rock chips, while the Novillo leather interior shows no bolster wear. This is a concours-ready example for the discerning collector seeking peak analog performance.",
